               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; the word sälam; the name of the donor (and his family members); several lines or groups of lines on the page opening the commemorative notices for each month; one or two initial lines of each commemorative notice; elements of the punctuation signs (e.g., nine dot asterisks in red and black, separating the commemoration notes); elements of Ethiopic numerals.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- On fol. 76vb, at the end of the month Gǝnbot, the scribe wrote the concluding prayer Zä-ʾaqräbku maḫletä… “The song I am offering…”, followed by a supplication of the scribe himself and the donor:</note>
                     <note>Fol. 76vc: ማኅበረ፡ ነቢያት፡ ወሐዋርያት፡ ማኅበረ፡ ጻድቃን፡ ወሰማዕት። ማኅበረ፡ ደናግል፡… ዘአንበብክሙ፡ ወዘተርጉምክሙ፡ ዘወሀብክሙ፡ መብዓ፡ ለቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ በጸሎተ፡ ኵሎሙ፡ ቅዱሳን፡ ወሰማዕት፡ ለጸሐፊሁ፡ ኃጥእ፡ ወምስኪን፡ ወልደ፡ ማርያማ። ወለዘአጽሐፊሁ፡ ወልደ፡ አረጋዊ።።። ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን፡ ወአሜን፡ ለይኩን፡ ለይኩን ።</note>
                     <note>The scribe’s name is Wäldä Maryam. Written by the same hand as the main text, except for the name "Wäldä ʾArägawi".</note>
                     <note>- The scribe wrote directives for the ministers as to when to read the concluding prayer Zä-ʾaqräbku maḫletä… “The prayer I have offered…” on fol. 162vb. That is on 6. Ṗagwǝmen it should be read one time and on 5. Ṗagwǝmen two times.</note>
                  </msItem>
